label.value: maintenance of postsynaptic density structure

value.value: A process which maintains the organization and the arrangement of proteins in the presynaptic density.

label.value: modification of synaptic structure

value.value: Any process that modifies the structure/morphology of a synapse.

definition.value: This class does not cover assembly or disassembly of synapses, only the modification/remodelling of existing ones.

label.value: modification of synaptic structure, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission via modification of the structure of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: chemical synaptic transmission, postsynaptic

value.value: The part of synaptic transmission occurring in the post-synapse: a signal transduction pathway consisting of neurotransmitter receptor activation and its effects on postsynaptic membrane potential and the ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol.

label.value: regulation of postsynaptic cytosolic calcium ion concentration

value.value: Any process that regulates the concentration of calcium in the postsynaptic cytosol.

label.value: calcium ion binding involved in regulation of postsynaptic cytosolic calcium ion concentration

value.value: The directed change of free calcium ion concentration in the postsynaptic cytosol via the reversible binding of calcium ions to calcium-binding proteins in the cytosol thereby modulating the spatial and temporal dynamics of changes in postsynaptic cytosolic calcium concentrations.

label.value: cytoplasmic region

value.value: Any (proper) part of the cytoplasm of a single cell of sufficient size to still be considered cytoplasm.

label.value: presynaptic cytoskeleton

value.value: The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the presynapse.

label.value: postsynaptic cytoskeleton

value.value: The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the postsynapse.

label.value: postsynaptic specialization

value.value: A network of proteins within and adjacent to the postsynaptic membrane. Its major components include neurotransmitter receptors and the proteins that spatially and functionally organize them such as anchoring and scaffolding molecules, signaling enzymes and cytoskeletal components.

label.value: glutamatergic postsynaptic density

value.value: The post-synaptic specialization of a glutamatergic excitatory synapse.

label.value: regulation of protein catabolic process at synapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating protein degradation at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of protein catabolic process at presynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating a catabolic process occurring at a presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of protein catabolic process at postsynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating a catabolic process occurring at a postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of translation at presynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of translation at postsynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: G protein-coupled neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: A G protein-coupled neurotransmitter receptor activity, occurring in the postsynaptic membrane, involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential.

label.value: monoatomic ion antiporter activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: Any ion antiporter activity, occurring in the postsynaptic membrane, that is involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential.

label.value: ATPase coupled ion transmembrane transporter activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: Any ATPase coupled ion transmembrane transporter activity, occurring in the postsynaptic membrane, that is involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential.

label.value: neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in regulation of presynaptic cytosolic calcium ion concentration

value.value: Any neurotransmitter receptor activity that is involved in regulating the concentration of calcium in the presynaptic cytosol.

label.value: neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic cytosolic calcium ion concentration

value.value: Any neurotransmitter receptor activity that is involved in regulating the concentration of calcium in the postsynaptic cytosol.

label.value: release of sequestered calcium ion into presynaptic cytosol

value.value: The process in which calcium ions sequestered in the endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus or mitochondria are released into the presynaptic cytosol.

label.value: release of sequestered calcium ion into postsynaptic cytosol

value.value: The process in which calcium ions sequestered in the endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus or mitochondria are released into the postsynaptic cytosol.

label.value: inorganic ion import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of inorganic ions from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: positive regulation of postsynaptic cytosolic calcium concentration

value.value: Any process that increases the concentration of calcium ions in the postsynaptic cytosol.

label.value: serotonin receptor activity

value.value: Combining with the biogenic amine serotonin and transmitting a signal across a membrane by activating some effector activity. Serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine) is a neurotransmitter and hormone found in vertebrates and invertebrates.

label.value: neurotransmitter receptor internalization

value.value: A receptor-mediated endocytosis process that results in the internalization of a neurotransmitter receptor.

label.value: endocytosed synaptic vesicle processing via endosome

value.value: The process in which endocytosed synaptic vesicles fuse to the presynaptic endosome followed by sorting of synaptic vesicle components and budding of new synaptic vesicles.

label.value: endocytosed synaptic vesicle to endosome fusion

value.value: Fusion of an endocytosed synaptic vesicle with an endosome.

label.value: regulation of neurotransmitter receptor activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neurotransmitter receptor activity. Modulation may be via an effect on ligand affinity, or effector function such as ion selectivity or pore opening/closing in ionotropic receptors.

label.value: neurotransmitter receptor regulator activity

value.value: A molecular function that directly (via physical interaction or direct modification) activates, inhibits or otherwise modulates the activity of a neurotransmitter receptor. Modulation of activity includes changes in desensitization rate, ligand affinity, ion selectivity and pore-opening/closing.

label.value: ligand-gated calcium channel activity

value.value: Enables the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ions by a channel that opens when a specific ligand has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.

label.value: regulation of action potential firing rate

value.value: Any process that regulates the frequency of action potentials in a spike train.

label.value: microtubule plus-end directed mitotic chromosome migration

value.value: The cell cycle process in which chromosomes that are laterally attached to one or more mitotic spindle microtubules migrate towards the spindle equator via plus-end-directed movement along the microtubules. This process is part of mitotic metaphase plate congression.

label.value: lateral attachment of mitotic spindle microtubules to kinetochore

value.value: The cellular process in which sister chromatids become laterally attached to spindle microtubules as part of mitotic metaphase plate congression. Attachment precedes migration along microtubules towards the spindle equator (metaphase plate).

label.value: regulation of action potential firing pattern

value.value: Any process that regulates the temporal pattern of a sequence of action potentials in a neuron.

label.value: microtubule lateral binding

value.value: Binding to the side of a microtubule.

label.value: action potential initiation

value.value: The initiating cycle of an action potential. In vertebrate neurons this typically occurs at an axon hillock. Not all initiated axon potentials propagate.

label.value: regulation of action potential firing threshold

value.value: Any process that regulates the potential at which an axon potential is triggered.

label.value: protein localization to axon

value.value: A process in which a protein is transported to or maintained in a location within an axon.

label.value: protein localization to cell wall

value.value: The process of directing proteins towards the cell-wall.

label.value: protein localization to spore cell wall

value.value: A process in which a protein is transported, tethered to or otherwise maintained in a spore cell wall.

label.value: (D)-2-hydroxyglutarate-pyruvate transhydrogenase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-2-hydroxyglutarate + pyruvate = alpha-ketoglutarate + D-lactate, with FAD functioning as an intermediate hydrogen acceptor.

label.value: extrinsic component of matrix side of mitochondrial inner membrane

value.value: The component of the matrix side of the mitochondrial inner membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that are loosely bound to one of its surfaces, but not integrated into the hydrophobic region.

label.value: matrix side of mitochondrial inner membrane

value.value: The side (leaflet) of the mitochondrial inner membrane that faces the matrix.

label.value: UDP-glucuronic acid dehydrogenase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucuronate + NAD+ = UDP-beta-L-threo-pentapyranos-4-ulose + CO2 + NADH + H+.

label.value: UDP-4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose formyltransferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: 10-formyltetrahydrofolate + UDP-4-amino-4-deoxy-beta-L-arabinopyranose = 5,6,7,8-tetrahydrofolate + UDP-4-deoxy-4-formamido-beta-L-arabinopyranose.

label.value: UDP-4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose aminotransferase

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-4-amino-4-deoxy-beta-L-arabinopyranose + 2-oxoglutarate = UDP-beta-L-threo-pentapyranos-4-ulose + L-glutamate.

label.value: undecaprenyl-phosphate 4-deoxy-4-formamido-L-arabinose transferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-4-deoxy-4-formamido-beta-L-arabinopyranose + ditrans,octacis-undecaprenyl phosphate = UDP + 4-deoxy-4-formamido-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl ditrans,octacis-undecaprenyl phosphate.

label.value: cardiac muscle cell membrane repolarization

value.value: The process in which ions are transported across the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell such that the membrane potential changes in the repolarizing direction, toward the steady state potential. For example, the repolarization during an action potential is from a positive membrane potential towards a negative resting potential.
